1) Faster spin = brighter LEDs  
2) Spin direction/speed = a “comet” that advances along the tube (right/left)

Here’s a tight, build-ready plan you can drop in without overthinking.

# Hardware (simple + robust)
- **Microcontroller:** ESP32 dev board
- **IMU (gyro):** MPU-6050 (reads angular velocity)
- **LEDs:** WS2812B strip (5 V), however many pixels your staff has
- **Power:** 18650 Li-ion + 5 V boost (for LEDs), 1000 µF cap across 5 V/GND, inline fuse (2–3 A)
- **Wiring**
  - MPU6050 SDA → ESP32 GPIO 21, SCL → ESP32 GPIO 22, VCC 3.3 V, GND GND
  - LED DIN → ESP32 GPIO 5 (with 330 Ω in series), LED 5 V and GND shared with ESP32 GND
  - Big cap across LED 5 V/GND, common grounds

# Control logic (what it does)
- Read **gyro Z** (spin around the staff’s long axis).
- **Direction** = sign of gyroZ → move comet right (positive) or left (negative).
- **Speed** = |gyroZ| → sets **brightness** and **step size**.
- Smooth the gyro to kill jitter (exponential filter).
- Optional “clean flow” feel: use **jerk** (change in speed) to shorten trail when choppy, lengthen when smooth.

# Drop-in Arduino code (ESP32 + FastLED + MPU6050)
Paste this into Arduino IDE (ESP32 board selected). Install libraries: `FastLED`, `Wire` (built-in). The MPU6050 here uses raw I²C; it’s minimal and works.

```cpp
#include <Wire.h>
#include <FastLED.h>

#define LED_PIN   5
#define NUM_LEDS  120        // set to your strip length
#define LED_TYPE  WS2812B
#define COLOR_ORDER GRB
CRGB leds[NUM_LEDS];

#define I2C_SDA 21
#define I2C_SCL 22

// MPU6050 registers
#define MPU_ADDR 0x68
#define REG_PWR1 0x6B
#define REG_GYRO_ZOUT_H 0x47

// Tunables
float alpha = 0.90f;       // smoothing (0–1): higher = smoother, slower
float stepScale = 0.015f;  // how fast the comet travels per dps of spin
int   minBright = 10;      // dim floor
int   maxBright = 255;     // top brightness
int   baseHue   = 160;     // cyan-ish; change for vibe
int   trailLenMin = 6;
int   trailLenMax = 28;

volatile float smoothedSpin = 0.0f;   // smoothed |gyroZ|
volatile float smoothedSign = 0.0f;   // smoothed signed gyroZ for direction
float lastSpin = 0.0f;
float jerk = 0.0f;

float pos = 0.0f;          // comet head position (float for subpixel motion)

int16_t readGyroZ() {
  Wire.beginTransmission(MPU_ADDR);
  Wire.write(REG_GYRO_ZOUT_H);
  Wire.endTransmission(false);
  Wire.requestFrom(MPU_ADDR, 2, true);
  int16_t z = (Wire.read() << 8) | Wire.read();
  return z;
}

// Convert raw to dps (°/s). MPU6050 default gyro scale is 131 LSB/(°/s)
inline float toDPS(int16_t rawZ) { return (float)rawZ / 131.0f; }

void setupMPU() {
  Wire.begin(I2C_SDA, I2C_SCL, 400000);
  delay(50);
  // wake MPU6050
  Wire.beginTransmission(MPU_ADDR);
  Wire.write(REG_PWR1);
  Wire.write(0x00);
  Wire.endTransmission();
  delay(100);
}

void setup() {
  FastLED.addLeds<LED_TYPE, LED_PIN, COLOR_ORDER>(leds, NUM_LEDS);
  FastLED.setBrightness(64);
  FastLED.clear();
  FastLED.show();

  setupMPU();
}

void loop() {
  // 1) Read gyro Z and convert to dps
  int16_t rawZ = readGyroZ();
  float dpsZ = toDPS(rawZ);        // signed: + clockwise, - counter
  float absZ = fabsf(dpsZ);

  // 2) Smooth
  smoothedSpin = alpha * smoothedSpin + (1.0f - alpha) * absZ;
  smoothedSign = alpha * smoothedSign + (1.0f - alpha) * dpsZ;

  // 3) Jerk (change in smoothed speed)
  jerk = 0.8f * jerk + 0.2f * fabsf(smoothedSpin - lastSpin);
  lastSpin = smoothedSpin;

  // 4) Map spin to brightness
  // 0–400 dps → minBright–maxBright (tweak 400 for your spin skill)
  int bright = map((int)smoothedSpin, 0, 400, minBright, maxBright);
  bright = constrain(bright, minBright, maxBright);
  FastLED.setBrightness(bright);

  // 5) Trail length reacts to flow cleanliness (smoother = longer)
  // jerk 0–30 → long→short
  int trail = (int)(trailLenMax - constrain(jerk, 0.0f, 30.0f) * (trailLenMax - trailLenMin) / 30.0f);
  trail = constrain(trail, trailLenMin, trailLenMax);

  // 6) Advance comet position by signed spin
  float dir = (smoothedSign >= 0.0f) ? 1.0f : -1.0f;
  float step = dir * (smoothedSpin * stepScale);   // pixels per frame
  pos += step;

  // wrap position around strip
  while (pos >= NUM_LEDS) pos -= NUM_LEDS;
  while (pos < 0)         pos += NUM_LEDS;

  // 7) Render comet: head at pos, trail behind
  fill_solid(leds, NUM_LEDS, CRGB::Black);
  int head = (int)pos;

  // color shifts slightly with speed for flair
  uint8_t hue = baseHue + (uint8_t)constrain((int)(smoothedSpin * 0.2f), 0, 80);

  // draw head
  leds[head] = CHSV(hue, 255, 255);

  // draw trailing pixels with falloff
  for (int i = 1; i <= trail; i++) {
    int idx = (int)(head - i);
    while (idx < 0) idx += NUM_LEDS;
    uint8_t val = (uint8_t)(255 * powf(0.85f, i));  // smooth falloff
    leds[idx] += CHSV(hue, 255, val);
  }

  // optional: tiny forward glow (gives “clean flow” look when fast)
  int ahead = (head + 1) % NUM_LEDS;
  leds[ahead] += CHSV(hue, 200, (uint8_t)constrain((int)(smoothedSpin * 0.4f), 0, 180));

  FastLED.show();
  // Frame pacing: faster update feels smoother during spin
  delay(10); // ~100 FPS; tweak if needed
}
```

## Tuning notes
- **Brightness curve:** change `map(..., 0, 400, ...)`. If you don’t spin that fast, drop 400 to ~250.
- **Comet speed:** adjust `stepScale`. More = faster travel per spin.
- **Direction:** automatically flips from gyro sign; if it feels reversed, multiply `dpsZ` by `-1`.
- **Wobble bamboo bonus:** spiral-wrap the LEDs; your natural wobble creates gorgeous helical trails.

## Safety quickies
- Fuse the battery and heat-shrink all joints.  
- Put a 330 Ω on the LED data line, 1000 µF across LED 5 V/GND.  
- Common ground between ESP32, LEDs, and IMU.

If you want a variant where slow, silky spins grow **longer trails** (instead of just brightness), swap the jerk logic for a **variance-of-spin** window. But this version will already give you exactly what you asked for: spin a little → dim, slow drift; spin hard and clean → the comet surges right and blazes.
